# UI Patterns

## Text & Buttons
- Primary HUD/meta/status: White text on dark backgrounds
- All buttons: White text (#ffffff) in normal and hover states
- On hover: Change background only, never text color
- Smooth transitions (0.2s)

## HUD Overlay
- Data overlays: Hidden by default; toggle via checkbox
- Draggable; position persists in localStorage
- Minimize button (-) in top-right collapses and unchecks checkbox
- Tabular layout prevents value jitter

## Controls Pattern
- Conceptual labels ("Resolution" not "Bucket Size")
- MAX/DEFAULT quick access buttons where appropriate
- Bidirectional controls: Two columns (HIGHER DETAIL vs LOWER DETAIL)
- Vertical stacking within columns

## Keyboard Shortcuts
- **Only use lowercase letters** for keyboard shortcuts (e.g., `"s"` not `["s", "S"]`)
- The browser automatically handles case-insensitive matching for letter keys
- Special keys like arrow keys, Escape, etc. should use their proper key names
- Disabled when typing in input fields

## Window Management
- When in "replace instance" mode, new windows should open on the same monitor and at the same upper-left corner position as the previous instance
- Prevents users from having to rearrange window positions

## Browser Extension Patterns
When building browser extensions:
- Follow manifest rules strictly (avoid inline css styles, onclick actions in HTML)
- Don't add security overrides; code the extension properly
- Keep dependencies minimal
- Focus on performance for quick loading
- Store user data locally when needed
- Follow browser extension security policies
- Use semantic HTML and accessible design
